<subSubSection id="A3D9BDBF9619D305F3E94C5F699082D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="49360B78DC2A04D964DB30294757EF1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7FE56188726F458C2260962F5CCD702A" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="7005C703AF9D822E9521CAAEAF31D830" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Gaujonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gaujonia bichu" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bichu">
<emphasis id="2839E1A3CE6F2CDAA9585961746E378C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Gaujonia bichu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens were found in Ecuador in coniferous and deciduous forests at high elevations above 2500 m (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="411F3F2656CAB1DF0D62E8BB7304E684" captionStart="Figure 93" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 93. Distribution of examined specimens of the genera Gaujonia and Gaujoptera." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.985.51622.figure93" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471615" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">93</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
